    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
      <p>This addition to the Milton L. Grigg Papers contains 910
         items, 1930-1981, chiefly the personal and research papers of
         Milton L. Grigg (1905-1982), a Charlottesville, Virginia,
         architect. These papers encompass the entire span of Grigg's
         career as an architect and reflect his specialization in
         church architecture, estates, restoration, and historic
         preservation. The collection includes: correspondence,
         publications, speeches, architectural drawings, pamphlets,
         printed material, photographs, newsclippings, book reviews,
         reports, and research files. A list of Grigg's architectural
         projects can be found in the control folder.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement>
      <head>Organization</head>
      <p>The topical organization of the collection has been
         maintained with minor modification and the folders are
         arranged alphabetically.</p>
    </arrangement>
